  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of life saving Nutrition and WASH Services to crisis affected population in Somali and Oromia regions of Ethiopia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of the proposed project is to undertaken nutrition interventions; the project will treat children with severe acute malnutrition (SAM) in the targeted Woredas in Oromia and Somali Regions. The targeted number of children to be treated with SAM will be 8,467 children (4,233 girls and 4,234 boys). Out of these, about 10 percent (847)) will be the target to be treated with SAM and underlying medical complications. Additionally, the project will aim at providing optimal preventive infant and young child feeding (IYCF) practices to approximately 90,186 pregnant and lactating women (PLW) and other caregivers of children. The WASH response will provide life-saving WASH services and supplies for the affected population reaching an anticipated 250,000 persons (directly).  The project provides life-saving assistance 327,653 people, including 133,696  women, 38,930 men and 155,027 children. This project will reach 59,270 People with disabilities</narrative>
  </description>
